      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="238">Cerium is isolated from the mineral monazite- CeP</text>
      <subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="238">O</text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="13" fc="0" fa="1" charset="238"></text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="238">4</text>
      </subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="238">. It is separated from other elements by ion-exchange chromatography. The usual method of cerium preparation is the electrolysis of molten cerium(III) chloride - CeCl</text>
      <subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="13" fc="0" fa="1" charset="238"></text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="13" fc="0" fa="1" charset="238"></text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="238">3</text>
      </subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0"> - or the reduction  of cerium(III) chloride by calcium or sodium.</text>
   </par>
